ng a nice wage this summer  ranging from  9 hour up to more than  30 hour  The days of unpaid internships in the business world are over   a mutually beneficial trend for cadets and employers  who often use the internship as an extended job interview  Given the continuing tough economic climate  cadets had to work hard to obtain these excellent opportunities  Working in conjunction with Linda Moreschi  EC BU Internship Coordinator  and our excellent staff in the Office of Career Services  cadets have located positions in the following companies  Bloomberg Global Data Owens   Minor Barclays LLC Caterpillar US Department of State US Department of Energy US Senate Northwestern Mutual Atlantic Credit   Finance Altria Northrup Grummon AOC Key Solutions Sam Segar   Associates Virginia Managed Investments Research Financial Strategies The cadets who will be earning credit for their internships have specific academic requirements  including setting learning objectives prior to starting  submitting weekly logs  writing a paper  and giving a presentation to the EC BU faculty when they return in the fall  Part of their grade also comes from an employer evaluation  As Cadet Chris Fraser  12 said of his 2010 internship for credit   Completing an internship for credit forces you to spend time reflecting on your experience in the working world  Not only does it allow you to make connections between academic lessons and the business world  it also gives you a chance to objectively gauge your internship and think about whether you d like to pursue a career in that line of work  The cadets pursuing credit work with the faculty advisor  Col Robert Moreschi  who oversees the academic component  Depending on the functional areas covered  cadets can earn up to three credits of either a business or economic elective  We are always looking for valuable internship opportunities for cadets  If you know of an available internship for the summer of 2012  please contact Linda Moreschi at moreschilp vmi edu or  540  464 7237  Spring 2011 Newsletter  Field Test  Faculty Research  TAPS  New Faculty  Lopez Chair  Alumni in the News  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  BGS   ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 